snippet: The endurance swimmer Diana Nyad, 64, on Monday became the first person to swim the 110 miles from Cuba to Key West, Fla., without a shark cage.
abstract: Endurance swimmer Diana Nyad becomes first person to swim 110-mile passage from Cuba to Florida without protection of a shark cage; it was her fifth attempt, completing quest that had bedeviled her for 35 years; survives nearly 53 hours in treacherous Florida Straits, notorious stretch of water brimming with sharks, jellyfish, squalls and an unpredictable Gulf Stream.
lead_paragraph: The endurance swimmer Diana Nyad, 64, on Monday became the first person to swim the 110 miles from Cuba to Key West, Fla., without a shark cage.

headline.main: Sharks Absent, Swimmer, 64, Strokes From Cuba to Florida
headline.print_headline: Sharks Absent, Swimmer, 64, Strokes From Cuba to Florida
